Nigeria Polling Unit Data Extractor & Sorter

This project provides an end-to-end workflow for scraping, cleaning, and organizing polling unit data from the INEC website (integrity.ng). The final output is structured Excel files grouped hierarchically by State → LGA → Ward → Polling Unit.

The tool supports data cleaning, normalization, and export into well-structured Excel sheets, making it useful for data verification, auditing, and civic tech analysis.

📁 Output Structure

For each state, a single Excel file (.xlsx) is generated containing three sheets:

Sheet Name	Description
State_LGA	Unique combinations of State and LGA
LGA_Wards	Unique combinations of LGA and Ward
LGA_Wards_PUs	Full dataset including LGA, Ward, and Polling Unit
🧠 How the Pipeline Works
1. Data Cleaning
Removes leading and trailing whitespace from all key fields:
State
LGA
Ward
Polling Unit
Drops duplicate records to ensure data consistency
2. Sorting & Grouping
Data is grouped by State
Within each state, data is organized as follows:
Sheet 1: State → LGA
Sheet 2: LGA → Ward
Sheet 3: LGA → Ward → Polling Unit

This ensures a clean hierarchical structure for analysis.

3. Excel Export
One Excel file is generated per state using pandas.ExcelWriter
Each file contains the three structured sheets listed above
⚠️ Important Notes on INEC Data Structure
❗ Column Mislabeling on INEC Website

A major issue discovered during scraping is inconsistent labeling on the INEC platform.

The actual data mapping is as follows:

Website Label	Actual Meaning
LGA	State
Ward	LGA
Polling Unit	Ward

This mismatch required adjustments in the data processing logic.

Always validate what each field represents based on content, not label names alone.

🛠 Dependencies
pandas
openpyxl (Excel export)
requests, BeautifulSoup, or selenium (for scraping, depending on implementation)
📦 Main File
final_work_done_by_jare.ipynb
Contains the full pipeline: scraping, cleaning, sorting, and export
🧹 Manual Data Cleaning Notes

After automated processing, additional manual cleaning was performed to refine the dataset.

Removed Columns

The following fields were excluded as they were not relevant to the core geographic structure:

PVC Count
Agent Name
Agent Contact
Other non-essential metadata fields

This helped focus the dataset strictly on electoral geography.

⚠️ Data Issues Observed

Some inconsistencies were found in the raw dataset:

1. Redundancy Issues
Duplicate State entries across multiple rows
Repeated LGAs not aligned with clean administrative grouping
Wards appearing multiple times due to inconsistent formatting
2. Source-Level Inconsistencies

These issues mainly originate from:

INEC website structure
Inconsistent naming conventions
Pagination and rendering behavior
🧾 Final Summary

This project combines:

Web scraping in Python
Data cleaning and normalization
Hierarchical data structuring
Excel report generation
Manual validation and refinement

Overall, it represents a complete data pipeline from raw extraction to structured output suitable for analysis and reporting.
